1.4 “Distribute” means to provide, publish, share, transmit, or otherwise make available
a copy of the Software or a Derivative Work to any third party by any means, including by
download, source control hosting, package registries, container registries, app stores, or
physical media.

1.5 “Derivative Work” means any work based on the Software for which Your modifications
(as a whole) would be considered an original work of authorship under applicable copyright law.
For clarity: modifications, forks, patches, refactors, ports, and additions that incorporate
any portion of the Software are Derivative Works.

1.6 “Fee” means any monetary or non-monetary consideration (including subscription payments,
license fees, access fees, usage fees, seat fees, revenue share, or any other thing of value)
that a recipient must provide as a condition to (a) obtain a copy of the Software/Derivative Work,
or (b) access or use the Software’s functionality.

1.7 “Hosted Service” means providing third parties access (directly or indirectly) to any
substantial set of the features or functionality of the Software or a Derivative Work over a network,
including SaaS, PaaS, hosted, managed service, or “X-as-a-service” offerings, regardless of whether
access is provided via a web UI, API, CLI gateway, embedded console, or similar interface.

1.8 “Customer Environment” means infrastructure and accounts that are owned or controlled by the
customer receiving Professional Services, where the customer has administrative control and can run
the Software independently.

1.9 “Professional Services” means human-delivered services such as consulting, installation,
configuration, integration, customization, training, security review, operations support, and
troubleshooting performed for a specific customer.

